Package: StatsEdSimData
Title: First Semester Statistics Course Data Simulator
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Keah", "Tandon", , "tandonk@mailbox.sc.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0009-2320-3082")),
    person("Michael", "Seaman", , "mseaman@sc.edu", role = "aut"))
Description: A tool for statistics educators to generate simulated data for all
    the major concepts in a first-semester statistics course. Functions include
    generating K groups/samples for binary, categorical, and quantitative data, 
    matched pairs quantitative data with specified parameters and/or moments.
    There is also a function for correlated quantitative data with specified
    moments, slope, and correlation coefficient. The quantitative variables are
    produced using Fleishman's power transformation method. You provide the 
    parameters, and we provide the data.
